The '''Bronko Nagurski Trophy''' has been awarded annually since 1993 to the [[college football|collegiate]] [[American football]] defensive player adjudged by the membership of the [[Football Writers Association of America]] (FWAA) to be the best in the [[National Collegiate Athletic Association]] (NCAA). The award is named for [[Bronko Nagurski]], who played football for the [[University of Minnesota]] and [[Chicago Bears]], and is presented by the Charlotte Touchdown Club and FWAA.<ref>{{cite news|title=College football: 2016 Bronko Nagurski Trophy watch list announced|url=https://www.ncaa.com/news/football/article/2016-07-08/college-football-2016-bronko-nagurski-trophy-watch-list-announced|access-date=July 5, 2017|work=NCAA.com|publisher=Football Writers Association of America|date=July 8, 2016}}</ref>

